<div id="review_308176502" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/308176502" />
    <a title="Yumi Learner" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7533642-yumi-learner"><img alt="Yumi Learner" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1333076992p2/7533642.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/308176502?book_show_action=true">Apr 07, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Yumi Learner" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Yumi Learner" href="/user/show/7533642-yumi-learner">Yumi Learner</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780142302309" href="/book/show/907890.Fudge_A_Mania">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer308176502" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18163875010729058286">A month ago I read &quot;Fudge-a-Mania&quot; in English without using a dictionary. The book is my American friend&apos;s recommendation. She suggested to me that the author&apos;s books are good for me to read. It was very true. She has written a bunch of books for children. Even thought I read the only one, it was very interesting, and I really enjoyed it.<br/><br/>It&apos;s bit difficult for mature English learners to find some interesting books for children in English. I&apos;d love to recommend the author&apos;s books for mature learn</span>
  <span id="freeText18163875010729058286" style="display:none">A month ago I read "Fudge-a-Mania" in English without using a dictionary. The book is my American friend's recommendation. She suggested to me that the author's books are good for me to read. It was very true. She has written a bunch of books for children. Even thought I read the only one, it was very interesting, and I really enjoyed it.<br /><br />It's bit difficult for mature English learners to find some interesting books for children in English. I'd love to recommend the author's books for mature learners.<br /><br />While I was in America last month, I bought some of her books at a second hand book store. Current, I've been reading "The Bridges of Madison County". After finishing reading it, I'd love to read all her books that I bought in America.</span>
  <a data-text-id="18163875010729058286" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
