<div id="review_2196075366" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2196075366" />
    <a title="Kayden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/70747984-kayden"><img alt="Kayden" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2196075366?book_show_action=true">Nov 26, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kayden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kayden" href="/user/show/70747984-kayden">Kayden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2196075366" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2736258595347385936">In this book Fudge-A-Mania I like many things. I liked how the author changed how she spelled words differently to show that someone had something in their mouth or some the difference in age and how a baby doesn&apos;t pronounce their words as good. That was able to put a good image in my head of what the situation was like. I really like how she put problems in this book of a real life family vacation. I was able to relate to a lot of Peter&apos;s problem&apos;s because they happen in my own family vacation.</span>
  <span id="freeText2736258595347385936" style="display:none">In this book Fudge-A-Mania I like many things. I liked how the author changed how she spelled words differently to show that someone had something in their mouth or some the difference in age and how a baby doesn't pronounce their words as good. That was able to put a good image in my head of what the situation was like. I really like how she put problems in this book of a real life family vacation. I was able to relate to a lot of Peter's problem's because they happen in my own family vacation. I liked how the author was able make Sheila in to this really bosy, known it all girl who was always trying to act grown up. Then also having Peter who was a normal teenage boy and have the natural boy, girl feud with Sheila. I thought it was also really funny how Fudge is trying to marry a girl so he won't have to worry about monsters in his room and how he thinks he is an expert on ladies. This was a really good book for someone that is looking for a quick easy book. Don't let me fool you though even though this is a quick and easy book it still has very good parts in it where you won't want to put it down. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2736258595347385936" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


